---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words with the Highest Points Per Tile — Efficiency Ranking"
  description="Most efficient Scrabble words ranked by points-per-tile ratio. QUIZ (22pts/4tiles=5.5ppt), ZAX (19pts/3tiles=6.3ppt). Maximize scoring efficiency per letter played."
  keywords="scrabble points per tile, most efficient scrabble words, quiz scrabble ratio, zax scrabble, points per letter scrabble, efficient scoring scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words with the Highest Points Per Tile — Efficiency Ranking","description":"Most efficient Scrabble words ranked by points-per-tile ratio. QUIZ (22pts/4tiles=5.5ppt), ZAX (19pts/3tiles=6.3ppt).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-highest-points-per-tile"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What Scrabble word has the highest points-per-tile ratio?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"ZAX scores 19 points from just 3 tiles (Z=10, A=1, X=8), giving it a ratio of 6.3 points per tile. It's a tool for cutting roofing slates and is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUIZ efficient in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Extremely. QUIZ scores 22 points from 4 tiles (Q=10, U=1, I=1, Z=10) for a 5.5 points-per-tile ratio. It uses both Q and Z — the two highest-value tiles — in one compact play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does points-per-tile matter in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Efficient words let you score high while using fewer tiles, leaving more options in your rack for future turns. A 3-tile word scoring 19 points (ZAX) is often better than a 7-tile word scoring 12 points because you keep 4 tiles for your next play."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words with the Highest Points Per Tile — Efficiency Ranking</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Raw points matter, but efficiency matters more. A 3-letter word scoring 19 points leaves you 4 extra tiles for your next turn — that's strategic advantage. This guide ranks Scrabble words by their points-per-tile (PPT) ratio, revealing the most efficient plays in the game.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6.3 ppt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZAX (19pts/3)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5.5 ppt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUIZ (22pts/4)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5.0 ppt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZAP (14pts/3)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4.7 ppt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JAB (12pts/3)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Most Efficient Words in Scrabble</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Highest Ratio</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ZAX — 6.3 Points Per Tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Z=10, A=1, X=8 · 19 pts from 3 tiles · Tool for cutting slates</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">ZAX achieves the highest PPT ratio of any common word. Using both Z (10pts) and X (8pts) in just 3 letters, it delivers premium-tile power while leaving 4 tiles on your rack for the next play. Maximum efficiency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📊 QUIZ</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">22 pts / 4 tiles = 5.5 ppt · Q=10, U=1, I=1, Z=10</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ ZAP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts / 3 tiles = 4.7 ppt · Z=10, A=1, P=3</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥊 JAB</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts / 3 tiles = 4.0 ppt · J=8, A=1, B=3</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 OX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts / 2 tiles = 4.5 ppt · O=1, X=8</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More High-Efficiency Words</h2>
      <p>These short words all exceed 3.0 points per tile:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts/2=4.5</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts/2=4.5</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts/2=5.5</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts/2=5.5</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts/2=4.5</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JEW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts/3=4.3</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Efficiency Beats Raw Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack preservation:</span> Playing ZAX (3 tiles, 19pts) leaves you with 4 tiles to draw into. A 7-letter word scoring 12pts uses all your tiles and gives you a random new rack.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> Short high-PPT words fit easily onto Double/Triple Letter squares. ZAX on a Triple Letter (Z) jumps to 39 points from just 3 tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tempo control:</span> High-efficiency plays keep the board tight while scoring well. You get points without opening scoring lanes for your opponent.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The magic PPT threshold is <span class="text-white font-medium">3.0 points per tile</span>. Any word above this outperforms the average 7-letter bingo (which scores ~10pts/7tiles = 1.4ppt before the bonus). ZAX (6.3), QUIZ (5.5), and QI (5.5) are the efficiency kings.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/high-scoring-short-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">High-Scoring Short Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/power-plays-under-5-tiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Power Plays Under 5 Tiles</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find the most efficient words for your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
